(Network Agent Project Report) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Project Overview and Goals) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Problem statement) Tj
T*
(Modern network outages are often diagnosed manually by stitching together partial evidence from) Tj
T*
(ping, traceroute, logs, and packet-level summaries. This process is slow, error-prone, and) Tj
T*
(highly dependent on operator experience. In classroom and small-team settings, this creates two) Tj
T*
(practical problems:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Analysts can miss obvious contradictions between data sources.) Tj
T*
(- Analysts can run unsafe or unnecessary commands while trying to collect more evidence.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(network-agent addresses this by implementing a multi-agent troubleshooting pipeline that) Tj
T*
(consumes user prompts and network artifacts, then produces a structured diagnosis with) Tj
T*
(confidence, required evidence, and remediation guidance.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Why this is interesting) Tj
T*
(This project is interesting from a systems and research perspective because it sits at the) Tj
T*
(intersection of:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Agent orchestration: planner, executor, generator, validator roles with explicit data) Tj
T*
(contracts.) Tj
T*
(- Safety-critical tooling: command allowlists, mutation detection, and approval gating.) Tj
T*
(- Hybrid reasoning: deterministic parser/rule logic augmented by optional LLM assistance.) Tj
T*
(- Cross-platform execution: Linux, macOS, and Windows command mapping and constraints.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The key design target is not ?maximal model creativity.? It is reliable, auditable diagnosis) Tj
T*
(under operational constraints.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Project goals) Tj
T*
(The system is designed around six concrete goals:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Classify incidents into common network categories.) Tj
T*
(- Select and run only safe, read-oriented diagnostics by default.) Tj
T*
(- Produce ranked causes with explicit confidence and evidence links.) Tj
T*
(- Preserve a trace of each agent stage for reproducibility.) Tj
T*
(- Support optional local/offline LLM assistance.) Tj
T*
(- Remain usable by instructors with straightforward run instructions.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Chosen Domain) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Domain choice) Tj
T*
(This project uses an Other approved domain: Network Troubleshooting Agent.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Domain-specific constraints) Tj
T*
(Compared with generic assistant tasks, this domain has strict requirements:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
