(- Inputs are heterogeneous and noisy \(logs, traceroute hops, packet summaries\).) Tj
T*
(- Suggested actions can have real operational risk if not constrained.) Tj
T*
(- Cross-platform command semantics differ \(traceroute vs tracert, interface commands, route) Tj
T*
(tools\).) Tj
T*
(- ?Correctness? often means ?best-supported hypothesis with evidence gaps identified,? not a) Tj
T*
(single exact answer.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Why this domain fits a multi-agent architecture) Tj
T*
(Each subproblem maps naturally to a specialized agent:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Planner handles triage and check selection.) Tj
T*
(- Executor handles data collection/parsing under policy constraints.) Tj
T*
(- Generator handles explanation and ranked causes.) Tj
T*
(- Validator handles constraint checks, confidence sanity checks, and safety consistency.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This separation improved maintainability and made testing easier because each stage has a narrow) Tj
T*
(contract.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Agent Architecture) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(High-level architecture) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(    flowchart TD) Tj
T*
(        U[User Prompt + Artifacts] --> P[Planner]) Tj
T*
(        P --> E[Executor]) Tj
T*
(        E --> G[Generator]) Tj
T*
(        G --> V[Validator]) Tj
T*
(        V --> R[Diagnosis + Remediation]) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(        OS[Host OS Profile] --> P) Tj
T*
(        OS --> E) Tj
T*
(        OS --> V) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(        SG[Safety Gate] --> E) Tj
T*
(        SG --> V) Tj
T*
(        A[Audit Logger] --> P) Tj
T*
(        A --> E) Tj
T*
(        A --> G) Tj
T*
(        A --> V) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Component responsibilities) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Planner) Tj
T*
(- Classifies incident category \(connectivity, dns, routing, transport, security, unknown\).) Tj
T*
(- Selects relevant checks for that category.) Tj
T*
(- Applies host-OS adaptations.) Tj
T*
