() Tj
T*
(- Validation and Safety Checks) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Safety model) Tj
T*
(Safety is implemented as a first-class constraint, not an afterthought.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- OS-specific command allowlist.) Tj
T*
(- Forbidden destructive tokens \(e.g., rm, shutdown, format\).) Tj
T*
(- Dual-use command mutation detection \(add, set, delete, etc.\).) Tj
T*
(- Explicit approval path for potential configuration-changing actions.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Structural and semantic checks) Tj
T*
(Validator logic checks for:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Presence of candidate causes.) Tj
T*
(- Confidence range consistency \(0..1\).) Tj
T*
(- Evidence sanity checks \(e.g., packet loss bounds\).) Tj
T*
(- Ambiguity detection and optional critic invocation.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Capture-duration controls) Tj
T*
(Live capture duration now includes controls to prevent runaway collection:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- CLI flag --capture-seconds with bounds \(5 to 300\).) Tj
T*
(- Prompt-based override parsing \(e.g., ?capture for 45 seconds?\).) Tj
T*
(- Timeout enforcement in shell runner with partial-output handling on timeout.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Testing evidence) Tj
T*
(The repository includes tests that cover:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Planner classification and OS behavior.) Tj
T*
(- Executor live collection behavior.) Tj
T*
(- Validator command blocking and approval path.) Tj
T*
(- Engine operation trace and integration outputs.) Tj
T*
(- LLM-path integration with mock provider.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Results and Discussion) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(What works well) Tj
T*
(- Deterministic baseline remains reliable) Tj
T*
(   The parser + heuristic pipeline yields consistent outputs across synthetic scenarios.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- LLM integration is optional and bounded) Tj
T*
(   LLM-assisted planning/generation can be enabled for richer behavior while preserving) Tj
T*
(deterministic fallback.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Safety constraints are explicit and testable) Tj
T*
(   Command gating, mutation detection, and approval paths are encoded in code and exercised in) Tj
T*
(tests.) Tj
T*
